Pseudocode for Advanced Arrays

Variables
    - hogDogItems: Array<String>, list of hot dog stand items
    - quantity: Array<String>, corresponding quantity to each hogDogItem


Process
    - Declare the hotDogItems and its quantity arrays
    - For loop to display items with their remaining quantity
    - Create a multidimensional array using hotDogItems and quantity
    - firstWay()
    - secondWay()

Functions

    firstWay()

        Variables
            - inventory: arrayOf<Array<String>>

        Process
            - append items array to inventory[0]
            - append quantity array to inventory[1]
            - access item and quantity by "there are ${inventory[1][i]} ${inventory[0][i]} left."

    secondWay()

        Variables
            - inventory: arrayOf<Array<String>>

        Process
            - append items[i] and quantity[i] to inventory[i]:
            - inventory[i][1] = items[i]
            - inventory[i][0] = quantity[i]
            - access item and quantity by "there are ${inventory[i][1]} ${inventory[i][0]} left."